.TH "gmap_shadow_pgt" 9 "gmap_shadow_pgt" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gmap_shadow_pgt \- instantiate a shadow page table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" gmap_shadow_pgt
.BI "(struct gmap *sg "  ","
.BI "unsigned long saddr "  ","
.BI "unsigned long pgt "  ","
.BI "int fake "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sg" 12
pointer to the shadow guest address space structure
.IP "saddr" 12
faulting address in the shadow gmap
.IP "pgt" 12
parent gmap address of the page table to get shadowed
.IP "fake" 12
pgt references contiguous guest memory block, not a pgtable
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 if successfully shadowed or already shadowed, -EAGAIN if the
shadow table structure is incomplete, -ENOMEM if out of memory,
-EFAULT if an address in the parent gmap could not be resolved and

Called with gmap->mm->mmap_lock in read
